statements: SELECT * FROM data_anomalies;
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_2 FROM data_anomalies;
SELECT feature_3, id, feature_1 FROM data_anomalies;
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_2, feature_3 FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_1 > 0.5;
SELECT id, feature_2 FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_2 < 0.3;
SELECT * FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_1 > 0.5;
SELECT id, feature_2 FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_1 < 0.3 ORDER BY feature_1 DESC;
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_3 FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_2 BETWEEN 0.1 AND 0.5 ORDER BY feature_3 ASC, feature_1 DESC;
SELECT AVG(feature_1) AS avg_feature1, COUNT(*) FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_3 < 0.2;
SELECT id, feature_1*feature_2 AS product FROM data_anomalies WHERE feature_1 > 0 ORDER BY product DESC;
